<Docs
  title="Privacy"
  description="Privacy notice for InfraNode: no cookies, no tracking, no ads, hosted in Germany."
  current="datenschutz"
  lang="en"
  altLangPath="/datenschutz/"
>
  <h1>Privacy</h1>

  <p>
    This site deliberately avoids any data processing beyond what is technically
    necessary to operate it.
  </p>

  <h2>No cookies, no tracking, no ads</h2>
  <p>
    This documentation site sets no cookies, embeds no analytics or tracking
    services and shows no ads. No profiles are built and no personal data is
    passed to third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Server logs</h2>
  <p>
    When the pages and the API are accessed, the hosting produces technically
    necessary server logs (for example IP address, time of the request, requested
    resource, user agent). This data serves secure and stable operation and the
    prevention of abuse. This data is not combined with other data sources.
  </p>

  <h2>Hosting</h2>
  <p>
    Operation takes place on a server in Germany (Nuremberg) at Hetzner Online
    GmbH, Industriestr. 25, 91710 Gunzenhausen, Germany. A data processing
    agreement under Art. 28 GDPR is in place with the provider.
  </p>

  <h2>Content delivery network (Cloudflare)</h2>
  <p>
    For secure and performant delivery and to mitigate attacks, I use the CDN of
    Cloudflare, Inc. (101 Townsend St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA). Cloudflare
    processes the IP address of the request. Transfer to the USA is safeguarded
    by the EU Standard Contractual Clauses. Cloudflare is certified under the
    EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
  </p>

  <h2>Reach measurement (technical, no cookies)</h2>
  <p>
    To detect active API users and to prevent abuse, hourly counts are kept on
    the server (IP address, user agent and the most recently requested path).
    This data is held in a volatile store (Redis) and automatically deleted
    after at most three hours. No cookies are set and no cross-device profiles
    are built. This measurement only concerns API requests, not visits to these
    documentation pages.
  </p>

  <h2>Operational notifications (ntfy)</h2>
  <p>
    To monitor API operation I send technical event notifications (including the
    requesting IP address, the user agent and the requested path) to the push
    notification service ntfy.sh. This too only concerns API requests, not
    visits to these documentation pages.
  </p>

  <h2>Legal basis</h2>
  <p>
    The legal basis for the processing described above is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR
    (legitimate interest in the secure, stable and abuse-free operation of the
    service). For contact by email the legal basis is Art. 6(1)(b) and (f) GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    If you contact me by email, I process the transmitted data solely to handle
    your request. Contact:
    <a href="mailto:admin@infranode.dev">admin@infranode.dev</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights under the GDPR</h2>
  <p>
    You have the rights to information, rectification, erasure, restriction of
    processing, data portability and objection. You also have the right to lodge a
    complaint with a data protection supervisory authority. For any request, reach
    me at <a href="mailto:admin@infranode.dev">admin@infranode.dev</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Controller</h2>
  <p>
    The controller for the processing is Khaled Cherif. The full provider details
    are in the <a href="/en/imprint/">Imprint</a>.
  </p>
</Docs>
